comments.comment_body:
@Carmine
Enough of the Dems are out to get Bernie stuff.  He’s at the top of the Progressive Wing right now and he doesn’t even bother to join and support the Democratic Party.  Seems he’s getting a fair shake to me.  There are plenty of people out here who don’t favor Sanders as the nominee.  Some of us see him as responsible for Trump once and could hold it against him.  The point is, if one is against Trump, one will vote for the nominee, period.  As I have said in these pages before, Sanders is my last choice, I will vote for him if he is the nominee.  Will you do the same if Sanders is not the nominee???  
In the meantime, I’m glad to see issues be openly debated within the party.  Thanks Mr Leonhardt for this column.
